# 7. つながる新年

Ichika: It's almost time... Oh!
Saki: Sorry, Ichi! Thanks for waiting!
Ichika: No, that's okay. I just got here a second ago. Anyway, shall we?
Saki: Hehe. The New Year's party at Shiho's is gonna be so much fun♪ I'm so excited that I brought a ton of mochi!
???: Hm...? What's this? Fancy seeing you two here.
Saki: Oh! Airi! Happy New Year!
Airi: Happy New Year! Are you two about to go somewhere?
Saki: Yes! We're going to Shiho's house.
Airi: Oh, nice! Sounds like you're both really enjoying New Year's♪
Ichika: We are. We just went to the beach yesterday to see the first sunrise, so we have been fairly busy...
Saki: And we got to be in Tsukasa and his troupe's show♪
Airi: Their show...?
Airi: Hang on. You're not talking about the one with the Lion Dance Deity, are you?
Saki: Huh? Yeah, it was that one! How did you know...?
Airi: Hehehe. We also got to participate in that very same show!
Saki & Ichika: What?!
Haruka: What? An, you saw that show too?
An: Yeah, they came to the ski resort we were at! And I didn't just watch... I sort of got to be in it.
Haruka: Really? We got to be in it too, as dancers from the village they were visiting.
An: Cool! So that's how your version went!
An: Wasn't it so much fun? I'd love to be in another show like that in the future.
Haruka: You definitely should. I think it suits you really well since you've got a lot of charisma.
An: Hehe. I just might if you want me to so much, Haruka. I mean, I can always switch tracks and try to become an actress...
Haruka: An actress...? That sounds nice, but is that what you really want to do?
An: Hmm... It seems like fun, but...
An: I'll pass! It's not what I want to do the most!
Haruka: Yeah, I had a feeling you'd say that.
An: Oh, my dear childhood friend! You know me too well♪
Waiter: Thank you for your patience! Here's your limited-edition New Year's penguin paradise parfait and rum raisin ice cream!
An: Oh, nice timing!
Haruka: It's so cute...! I have to take a picture...!
Mafuyu: Wait, Hinomori... You also got to see that show?
Shizuku: Yes, I did! It's incredible that they also did a performance at the mall. I really had no idea...
Mafuyu: I agree. They must've been very active throughout New Year's Day...
Mafuyu: At the same time, you just climbed a mountain yesterday, and you're about to go shopping with Momoi, no?
Shizuku: Hehe. There's a sweets shop that sells this red bean soup that I've been meaning to try. Would you like to join us, Asahina?
Mafuyu: Maybe. I still have some time until I need to meet back up with my family...
???: Huh? Mafuyu? And Shizuku?!
Mafuyu: Huh? Mizuki...?
Shizuku: Hi, Mizuki! Oh, you have company. What brings you all here today...?
Akito: Hello. And Happy New Year.
Mizuki: Oh, right! Happy New Year, Shizuku! We actually just ran into each other a second ago!
Mizuki: Li'l Bro here said that he's gonna go try the red bean soup at that shop over there, so I decided to tag along♪
Shizuku: Oh, I see! Airi and I are here to do the same thing. I'll be meeting her there.
Shizuku: Why don't we all go together? You too, Asahina. How does that sound...?
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu: I suppose I can stay until I hear from my family...
Shizuku: Really? Thank you!
Mizuki: Oh, Mafuyu, you gotta hear this! Li'l Bro said he and his team also saw Tsukasa's show!
Mafuyu: What?
Toya: It was a wonderful, happy show to welcome in the new year.
Akito: To be fair, seeing that Lion Dance Robot wandering around startled a lot of us...
Shizuku: Lion Dance Robot...? We saw that show too!
Mizuki: Wait, Shizuku, you did? Talk about a big coincidence!
Mizuki: Then, let's talk more about it over at the cafe! C'mon, you guys!
Kanade: Huff... Huff...
Honami: Are you okay, Ms. Yoisaki? You're carrying quite a lot, so maybe we should stop and take a break.
Kanade: I-I'm so sorry, Ms. Mochizuki... I didn't mean for this to happen when I asked you to go shopping with me...
Kanade: You're going over to your friend's house this afternoon for a party, yes? If you're pressed for time, please feel free to go...
Honami: Hehe. It's okay. I still have plenty of time.
Honami: More importantly... I hope you find a nice place in your father's hospital room for that mini mochi set that you just bought.
Kanade: Me too... We always have it on display during New Year's, so I hope he likes it...
???: Huff... Huff... Maybe I should stop here... Plus, it's freezing...
Ena: Huh...? That looks like... Kanade?! Honami?!
Kanade: Ena...?!
Ena: Wh-What are you two doing here?!
Kanade: We were just out shopping... What were you doing just now, Ena? Running?
Ena: Oh, so...
Ena: (Wait, I can't tell them that I'm running because I ate too much during the holidays and how Akito's poking fun at me for it...!)
Ena: R-Remember that show we saw yesterday by that troupe from PXL...?
Ena: Seeing that made me want to be more active... Haha...
Honami: PXL...? Are you talking about the show that Emu's troupe did?
Kanade: Huh? Wait, Ms. Mochizuki, did you also see it?
Honami: Um... Yes, but not at the mall. I saw it at the beach...
Kanade & Ena: The beach?!
Shiho: So, to summarize...
Shiho: After doing a show at the beach, Tsukasa and his troupe did another one on top of a mountain and then at a ski resort...?
Minori: Th-That's amazing...! It's like a surprise tour!
Kohane: The show itself was really short, but it must've been really hard to pull off something like that...!
Minori: At the same time, it's must've been really fun! A concert tour's one thing... But a show tour!
Shiho: It actually seems like something they'd do...
Minori: Yeah, I agree! Oh, Shiho, sorry for keeping you! We know you have a New Year's party to get to...!
Shiho: No, don't mind me. I still have some time until we're supposed to meet up.
Shiho: You two are meeting up with Kiritani and Shiraishi, right? Try not to be late, okay?
Kohane: Oh, right! They said that they're already there, so maybe we should get going.
Minori: Okay! Oh, Shiho...!
Shiho: Hm? Yeah?
Minori: I nearly forgot to say... Happy New Year!
Kohane: Let's go to PXL together again sometime.
Shiho: Hehe. Sure. And Happy New Year to the both of you.
